---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "JEPI Dividend Analysis & History",
    "description": "Discover the latest data on JEPI's dividend yield, payout frequency, and historical performance.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Fundamentals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the jepi dividend yield?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "As of the most recent data, JEPI features a notable 12-month trailing yield around 7.91%. It pays monthly distributions driven by options premiums and equity dividends."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Where can I find the jepi dividend history?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "JEPI's dividend history showcases varying monthly payouts depending on market volatility and covered call premiums. We track the last 5 years of distributions in our comprehensive data tables."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What was the jepi dividend yield 2024?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "In 2024, JEPI's yield typically fluctuated between 7% and 9% depending on the month's options income, maintaining its status as a high-income vehicle."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the expected jepi dividend yield 2025?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "While exact future yields are unpredictable, projections for the jepi dividend yield 2025 remain in the high single digits, assuming consistent market volatility."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Will the jepi dividend yield 2026 stay high?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The jepi dividend yield 2026 will largely depend on VIX levels and option premiums at that time. Lower volatility could compress the yield, while higher volatility may expand payouts."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout
  site="westmount"
  title="JEPI Dividend Analysis & History"
  description="Is the JEPI dividend yield sustainable? We analyze the exact payout history, P/E ratio, and project your future income with our calculator."
  canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/jepi-dividend"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>JEPI Dividend Analysis & History</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Complete yield metrics, 5-year payout history, and interactive income calculator</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>JEPI Dividend Profile</h2>
      <p>The JPMorgan Equity Premium Income ETF (JEPI) has become a cornerstone for income investors. Combining a defensive equity portfolio with a covered call overlay, it aims to deliver double-digit yields and lower volatility than the S&P 500.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Current Yield & Metrics</h3>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Current Trailing Yield</th>
              <td>7.91%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Payout Frequency</th>
              <td>Monthly</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Price-to-Earnings (P/E)</th>
              <td>26.62</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Expense Ratio</th>
              <td>0.35%</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>Investors should note that JEPI's distributions are variable. Because a significant portion of the yield comes from options premiums (ELNs), payouts naturally rise when market volatility (VIX) is high and compress during periods of market calm. You can compare this strategy to other high-income options in our <a href="/high-dividend-stocks">High Dividend Stocks analysis</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5-Year Dividend History</h2>
      <p>Reviewing the exact payout history is crucial for understanding income consistency. Below is the recent dividend distribution data for JEPI.</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Ex-Dividend Date</th>
            <th>Amount ($)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>2026-03-02</td><td>$0.3510</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2026-02-02</td><td>$0.3440</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-12-31</td><td>$0.4270</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-12-01</td><td>$0.3710</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-11-03</td><td>$0.3460</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-10-01</td><td>$0.3610</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-09-02</td><td>$0.3680</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-08-01</td><td>$0.3580</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-07-01</td><td>$0.4000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-06-02</td><td>$0.5400</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-05-01</td><td>$0.4880</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-04-01</td><td>$0.4080</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-12-31</td><td>$0.3950</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-12-02</td><td>$0.4020</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-11-01</td><td>$0.3750</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-10-01</td><td>$0.3920</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2023-12-28</td><td>$0.4280</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2023-12-01</td><td>$0.3900</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2022-12-29</td><td>$0.5730</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2022-12-01</td><td>$0.6100</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2021-12-30</td><td>$0.4590</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2021-12-01</td><td>$0.3830</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p><em>*Table displays a curated sample of monthly payouts across the last 5 years.</em></p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Dividend Reinvestment Calculator</h2>
      <p>Use our interactive calculator to estimate your annual income based on the current trailing yield. If you are exploring broad market growth instead, check our <a href="/voo-dividend">VOO Dividend Analysis</a>.</p>

      <div class="card" id="calc-container">
        <label style="display:block; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Number of Shares Owned</label>
        <input type="number" id="sharesInput" placeholder="e.g. 100" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary); font-size:1rem; margin-bottom:1rem;" />

        <label style="display:block; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Average Price per Share ($)</label>
        <input type="number" id="priceInput" placeholder="e.g. 58.00" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary); font-size:1rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem;" />

        <button id="calculateBtn" style="background:var(--accent-color); color:#fff; padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; border:none; border-radius:8px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer; width:100%; font-size:1rem;">Calculate Income</button>

        <div id="results" style="display:none; margin-top:1.5rem; padding-top:1.5rem; border-top:1px solid var(--border-color);">
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
            <span style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Estimated Annual Income:</span>
            <span id="annualIncome" style="font-weight:700; color:var(--accent-color);">$0.00</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between;">
            <span style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Estimated Monthly Payout:</span>
            <span id="monthlyIncome" style="font-weight:700;">$0.00</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the jepi dividend yield?</summary>
        <p>As of the most recent data, JEPI features a notable 12-month trailing yield around 7.91%. It pays monthly distributions driven by options premiums and equity dividends.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Where can I find the jepi dividend history?</summary>
        <p>JEPI's dividend history showcases varying monthly payouts depending on market volatility and covered call premiums. We track the last 5 years of distributions in our comprehensive data tables.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What was the jepi dividend yield 2024?</summary>
        <p>In 2024, JEPI's yield typically fluctuated between 7% and 9% depending on the month's options income, maintaining its status as a high-income vehicle.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the expected jepi dividend yield 2025?</summary>
        <p>While exact future yields are unpredictable, projections for the jepi dividend yield 2025 remain in the high single digits, assuming consistent market volatility.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Will the jepi dividend yield 2026 stay high?</summary>
        <p>The jepi dividend yield 2026 will largely depend on VIX levels and option premiums at that time. Lower volatility could compress the yield, while higher volatility may expand payouts.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const btn = document.getElementById('calculateBtn');
      const sharesInput = document.getElementById('sharesInput');
      const priceInput = document.getElementById('priceInput');
      const resultsDiv = document.getElementById('results');
      const annualSpan = document.getElementById('annualIncome');
      const monthlySpan = document.getElementById('monthlyIncome');

      const YIELD = 0.0791; // 7.91%

      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const shares = parseFloat(sharesInput.value) || 0;
        const price = parseFloat(priceInput.value) || 0;

        const totalValue = shares * price;
        const annual = totalValue * YIELD;
        const monthly = annual / 12;

        annualSpan.textContent = '$' + annual.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
        monthlySpan.textContent = '$' + monthly.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});

        resultsDiv.style.display = 'block';
      });
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    th, td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
